The paper deals with the problem of learning a discriminative latent-variable model, specifically a mixture of linear regressions. This falls under the broad category of machine learning, which is covered by cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also involves statistical analysis and estimation, which could fall under cs.ST (Statistics), and the use of low-rank linear regression and tensor factorization, which could fall under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). Finally, the paper involves optimization techniques, which could fall under cs.IT (Information Theory).
